A roadside bomb killed one Iraqi army officer and injured three of his soldiers in an attack on a patrol in Al-Garma near the city of Fallujah. No group claimed responsibility for the bombing.
Members of the security services are frequently targeted by various militant groups including the Al-Qaeda affiliated Islamic State of Iraq (ISI) which is active in Anbar province.
